# eqword2llm

[![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/eqword2llm.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/py/eqword2llm)
[![Python](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/eqword2llm.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/eqword2llm/)
[![CI](https://github.com/manabelab/eqword2llm/actions/workflows/ci.yml/badge.svg)](https://github.com/manabelab/eqword2llm/actions/workflows/ci.yml)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)

**Equation Word â†’ LLM**: Convert equation-heavy Word documents (.docx) to Markdown with LaTeX math for LLM recognition.

## Why eqword2llm?

Most Word-to-Markdown converters **ignore or break mathematical equations**. `eqword2llm` is specifically designed for **scientific and technical documents** where math equations are critical.

```
ğŸ“„ Word Document          â†’    ğŸ“ Markdown + LaTeX
â”Œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”        â”Œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”
â”‚ xÂ² + yÂ² = zÂ²        â”‚        â”‚ $x^{2} + y^{2} = z^{2}$
â”‚                     â”‚   â†’    â”‚                     â”‚
â”‚    a                â”‚        â”‚ $$\frac{a}{b}$$     â”‚
â”‚   â”€â”€â”€               â”‚        â”‚                     â”‚
â”‚    b                â”‚        â”‚                     â”‚
â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”˜        â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”˜
